result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Alicia P Babler in court with attorney Maris Rushevics. David R. Knaapen appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
All files heard: 13CF245, 14CF170, 14CF188, 13CV68

Plea questionnaire/Agreement filed.
Prosecutor states plea agreement.
  14CF170 State does not object expungment on the felony.  Defendant agrees to have the money seized in 13CV68 be forfeited. 
Attorney for Defendant concurs with agreement stated.

Defendant enters a plea of: 
13CF245 Counts 3, 4 and 5 - NO CONTEST
14CF170 Count 1 - NO CONTEST

Court questions Defendant regarding plea.
Court informs Defendant of Constitutional Rights. Court advises Defendant of Elements State must prove for the Charge.
Court questions Attorney for Defendant.
Court finds Defendant's Plea is freely, voluntarily and intelligently made.
Attorneys stipulate that there is factual basis for the charge(s).

BY THE COURT:
Court finds a sufficient factual basis to support the charge(s).
Court finds the defendant guilty 13CF245 Counts 3, 4 & 5, 14CF170 Count 1.  Clerk directed to enter Judgment of Conviction this date.
The following are dismissed and read-in: 
13CF245 Counts 1, 2 and 6 thru 9
14CF170 Counts 2 & 3
14CF188

Atty Knaapen makes sentencing arguments to the Court. 
Atty Rushevics makes sentencing arguments to the Court. 
Defendant makes statements to the Court. 

BY THE COURT: 
13CF245 Count 3 - 
100 days jail, Imposed and Stayed
No credit.
Placed on probation for a period of 24 months:
AODA & comply with treatment recommendations, if there are any.
Do not possess/consume controlled substances without a valid prescription and be taken according to the prescription. 
Get all prescription medications from one pharmacy.
Sign necessary release so agent can monitor when medications are prescribed by talking to doctors and pharmacists.
Do not possess any drug paraphernalia. 
Do not associate with any persons possessing or consuming illegal controlled substances.
Engage in any counseling deemed appropriate by the agent. 
Pay costs including VWS and filing fee. 

13CF245 Count 4 -
30 days jail, Imposed and Stayed - consecutive to any sentence she might be serving.
No credit.
Placed on probation for a period of 24 months, concurrent.
Comply with all conditions set forth in Count 3. 
Pay costs of VWS and filing fee. 

13CF245 Count 5 -
20 days jail, Imposed and Stayed - consecutive to any sentence she might be serving.
No credit.
Placed on probation for a period of 24 months, concurrent.
Comply with all conditions set forth in Count 3. 
Pay costs of VWS and filing fee. 

14CF170 Count 1 - 
Sentence withheld.
4 days of credit on this file only, if revoked.
Placed on probation for a period of 24 months, concurrent.
Comply with all conditions set forth in 13CF245 Count 3. 
Pay costs of VWS, filing fee and DNA surcharge.
Submit a DNA sample. 
Court will allow this sentence be under 973.015. 
Court will allow for early discharge after 18 months if the agent recommends and she has been in full compliance with all conditions. 

BY THE COURT: Any money posted in any of the files shall be used to pay the costs that have been ordered in all of these cases. If there is any balance due and owing, that is payable while she is on probation. 

Court advises defendant of voting, firearms rights. 

BY THE COURT:  13CV68 - By agreement, the $671.00 is ordered forfeited.
Plea hearing on December 9, 2014 at 03:00 pm.
